originalText.text: Best place to park your car if you’re in NYC then. They have franchises parking spaces all around the NYC. Your car is safe here so you don’t have to worry about car damages.

originalText.text: The biggest outdoor parking facility I've ever experienced in NYC, airport parking, excluded. Fast and friendly service, price reasonable given its location (close to the Lincoln Tunnel on the westside). We parked in town, on one of those busy evenings at the Garden; I believe it was a hockey game just before Christmas 23'. It was packed - that was the point of reference. They have an electronic system that keeps the rotation of paying your bill, queing your car and the attendant pulling up or handing you the keys. Seemed to work smooth for everyone waiting. That heated sunporch, though, was a bonus! Many people fit under while we awaiting our vehicles.

originalText.text: Booked reservation through SpotHero ($60/day), staff was very friendly upon pick up and drop off. I was told by a few of the other people while we were waiting for our cars that this was the best place to park in NYC.

originalText.text:
I have a Sprinter van, which can be difficult to find parking for in NY, but I was glad they accepted me. However, upon arrival, I told the valets that I would be parking there for 3 days and I asked what the rate would be. They went to the manager and came back to tell me it would be $150. It sounded good to me so I accepted and parked my van here. When I arrived 2 days and 5 hours later to pay and leave, the manager informed me it would be $430!! I argued and asked for their written pricing because I wanted them to justify how they arrived at that price. He then pulled out a random binder with a pricing table and no specifics. I told him I would pay $150 because that's what I was originally told and he said I wouldn't be leaving the lot then. He said I could get the police involved if I wanted to.

I then stated if I was going to pay that much then I should get monthly parking, based on the pricing on their signage as you can see in my picture. If course, he said they aren't doing monthly parking right now.

The whole thing is a bait and switch and I wasn't the only customer arguing about the pricing being misrepresented. The manager, Jean had a line of people waiting to speak with him. If I wasn't in a hurry to get back to my job site then I would have loved to take him up on  his offer to get the police involved because this place is a scam!

originalText.text:
Smooth and easy parking. The best rate in the area (based on ParkWhiz app comparative pricing). The parking is ideal for B&H Photo customers, Madison Square Garden visitors and other adjacent points of interest.
For NJ, PA and people heading to NJ Turnpike, the parking location is ideal, for it is practically right next door to Lincoln tunnel.
A separate pedestrian area and walkway are provided, next to the parking attendant booth.
For holders of ParkWhiz or any other pre-paid parking reservations, scan your parking ticket first, select the specific app, scan your parking app QR code and you are all set.
Happy parking.
